rustc --version # see the version of rust running A Macro is a pre-defined sequence of automated input, designed to streamline repetitive tasks. In Rustc: using a "!" means that you’re calling a macro instead of a normal function and that macros don’t always follow the same rules as functions.
2.title: Rust

3.body:
Cargo is Rust’s build system and package manager. In Rust, libraries are called dependencies. All code must be in src folder. Cargo Cheatsheet: Create Project cargo new folder_name
# creates a new folder with cargo.toml and src which has main.rs file.
# Also generates new git repository along with .gitignore file. # If a parent folder is git repo, it doesn't generate
cargo new --vcs=git # this overrides that behavour cargo new --help # see availabe options Build Project and run execulable cargo build
./target/build/folder_name Build and run project in one step cargo run check for error without creating any binary cargo check # quickly checks code to make sure it compiles but doesn't produce executable cargo stores build file in target/debug directory Building for release cargo build --release # compile with optimization
# creates executable in target/release instead of target/debug
